The ARM validator does not follow Google coding standards. This has serious negative implications for maintainability that must be addressed before it goes into production. Specific things I'm noticing:
- use of infix operators
- non-standard procedure names like &amp;quot;validator&amp;quot; and &amp;quot;copy_code&amp;quot;

As a part of productizing this code we need a plan to address this. Specifically:
- Are we going to allow style rule exceptions in this code? If so every exception must be documented and justified
- For issues to be fixed, if the will not be fully addressed before launch, we need a written plan that all parties agree on for what style issues will be fixed when.
